### Server Configuration
- `PORT`: Port number for the server (default: 5000)
- `NODE_ENV`: Environment mode - 'development', 'production', 'test' (default: development)

### Database Configuration (PostgreSQL)
- `DB_DIALECT`: Database dialect - 'postgres' (default: postgres)
- `DB_HOST`: PostgreSQL host (default: localhost)
- `DB_PORT`: PostgreSQL port (default: 5432)
- `DB_NAME`: Database name (default: careerlens)
- `DB_USER`: Database username (default: postgres)
- `DB_PASSWORD`: Database password (default: password)

### AI Service Configuration
- `AI_SERVICE_URL`: URL of the AI inference service (default: http://localhost:8000)
- `AI_SERVICE_TIMEOUT`: Timeout for AI service calls in milliseconds (default: 30000)

### CORS Configuration
- `CORS_ORIGIN`: Allowed origin for CORS (default: http://localhost:3000)

### Logging
- `LOG_LEVEL`: Logging level - 'error', 'warn', 'info', 'debug' (default: info)

## Example .env file

```bash
# Server
PORT=5000
NODE_ENV=development

# Database (PostgreSQL)
DB_DIALECT=postgres
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=careerlens
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=password

# AI Service
AI_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:8000
AI_SERVICE_TIMEOUT=30000

# CORS
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=info
```

## Production Deployment

For production, set:
- `NODE_ENV=production`
- `PORT=5000` (or your preferred port)
- `CORS_ORIGIN=https://yourdomain.com`
- Database settings according to your production PostgreSQL instance
- `AI_SERVICE_URL=https://your-ai-service.com`

